{
  "text": "The pigs were anesthetized with ketamine (10 mg/kg im), intubated, and maintained with isofluorane (2-4% in air supplemented with 1 l/min oxygen). A median sternotomy was performed, and the pigs were placed on positive pressure ventilation. Arterial blood gases were monitored, and the ventilator was adjusted to maintain pH 7.35-7.45, PCO [CITATION_1] 35-45 mmHg, and PO2 Ͼ100 mmHg.",
